716307f-a.text:
Amsterdam Avenue, north from W. 119th Street, showing a distant perspective from the heights occupied by Columbia University. The fenced corner at the left and the 120th-121st Street row of buildings to the north are a part of same, tho the latter are technically: The Lowell, Longfellow Hall, Whittier Hall and the Emerson of the Horace Mann School. At the foot of the hill is the Valley containing W. 125th Street. Beyond same begins the Washington Heights area of today.
November 1914
Geo. L. Balgue
